In mathematics, the '''Bott cannibalistic class''', introduced by {{harvs|txt|first=Raoul|last=Bott|year=1962|authorlink=Raoul Bott}}, is an  element <math>\theta_k(V)</math> of the [[representation ring]] of a [[compact Lie group]] that describes the action of the [[Adams operation]] <math>\psi^k</math> on the [[Thom class]] <math>\lambda_V</math> of a complex [[Representation of a Lie group|representation]] <math>V</math>. The term "cannibalistic" for these classes was introduced by {{harvs|txt|first=Frank|last=Adams|authorlink=Frank Adams|year=1965|loc=p.151}}.

