'''Elizabeth Spencer Allman''' (born 1965)<ref>Birth year from [http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no96019330.html Library of Congress catalog entry], retrieved 2018-12-01.</ref> is an American mathematician. She is a professor of mathematics in the Department of Mathematics and Statistics at the [[University of Alaska Fairbanks]].<ref>[http://www.dms.uaf.edu/~eallman/ Elizabeth S. Allman]</ref>
Allman earned her Ph.D. in 1995 from the [[University of California, Los Angeles]] under the supervision of Murray M. Schacher.<ref>{{mathgenealogy|name=Elizabeth Spencer Allman|id=36667}}.</ref> In 2012, Allman became a Fellow of the [[American Mathematical Society]].<ref>[http://www.ams.org/profession/fellows-list List of Fellows of the American Mathematical Society]</ref>
With her Fairbanks colleague John A. Rhodes, she is the author of the book ''Mathematical Models in Biology: An Introduction'' (Cambridge University Press, 2004).<ref>{{citation|title=Mathematical Models in Biology: An Introduction|department=Book Review|journal=Mathematical Medicine and Biology|year=2005|doi=10.1093/imammb/dqi008|first=N. F.|last=Britton}}.</ref><ref>{{citation|title=Mathematical Models in Biology: An Introduction|department=Book Review|journal=Mathematics and Computer Education|volume=39|issue=1|year=2005|last=Rauff|first=James V.|pages=78–79}}.</ref><ref>{{citation|title=Mathematical Models in Biology: An Introduction by E. S. Allman; J. A. Rhodes; Essential Mathematical Biology by N. F. Britton|first=Nick|last=Lord|journal=[[The Mathematical Gazette]]|volume=89|issue=514|year=2005|pages=173–175|jstor=3620700}}.</ref><ref>{{citation|title=Mathematical Models in Biology: An Introduction by Elizabeth S. Allman; John A. Rhodes|first=Mei|last=Zhu|journal=[[SIAM Review]]|volume=46|issue=3|year=2004|pages=593–595|jstor=20453561}}.</ref>
