In [[finite group|finite]] [[group theory]], a mathematical discipline, the '''Gilman–Griess theorem''', proved by {{harv|Gilman|Griess|1983}}, classifies the finite [[simple group|simple]] [[groups of characteristic 2 type]] with ''e''(''G'')&nbsp;≥&nbsp;4 that have a "standard component", which covers one of the three cases of the [[trichotomy theorem]].

