In [[mathematics]], a '''Koecher–Maass series''' is a type of [[Dirichlet series]] that can be expressed as a [[Mellin transform]] of a [[Siegel modular form]], generalizing Hecke's method of associating a Dirichlet series to a [[modular form]] using Mellin transforms. They were introduced by {{harvs|txt|last=Koecher|authorlink=Max Koecher|year=1953}} and {{harvs|txt|last=Maass|authorlink=Hans Maass|year=1950}}.

