In [[mathematics]], the '''Kronheimer–Mrowka basic classes''' are elements of the second [[cohomology]] H<sup>2</sup>(''X'') of a simple smooth 4-[[manifold (mathematics)|manifold]] ''X'' that determine its [[Donaldson polynomial]]s. They were introduced by {{harvs|txt | last1=Kronheimer | first1=P. B.| author1-link=Peter Kronheimer| last2=Mrowka | first2=Tomasz S. |author2-link=Tomasz Mrowka|  year1=1994 |year2=1995}}.

